{"type":"message","id":"dea7745a","parentId":"7f291783","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:19:54.375Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"snd keep firing\" - this seems like a reference to the Sandman (snd) sandbox pulse script. Let me check what's going on with the sandbox pulse. According to TOOLS.md, there's a \"Sandbox Pulse\" Task Scheduler job every 30 min, 8am-11pm ET.\n\nIt's 1:19 AM - well outside the scheduled hours (8am-11pm). So the pulse shouldn't be firing at all. Maybe the Task Scheduler job is misconfigured and running anyway?\n\nLet me check the pulse.ps1 script and the Task Scheduler configuration to understand what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"0e814261061affe5020b557ded643ad301f43f0c9334ebeb951e3627fa5e77d6"},{"type":"text","text":"That's weird — the Sandbox Pulse is supposed to only run 8am–11pm ET. It's 1:19 AM right now. Let me check what's configured and why it keeps firing.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_087raxepq393_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_087raxepq393_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ScheduledTask | Where-Object {$_.TaskName -like \"*pulse*\"} | Get-ScheduledTaskInfo | Select-Object TaskName, LastRunTime, NextRunTime, State"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":260,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":227,"totalTokens":12817,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774156787923}}
{"type":"message","id":"9a19ae1c","parentId":"dea7745a","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:19:54.563Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_087raxepq393_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files, decide, act, log, exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\",\n    [string]$LLMApiKey = \"\",  # Set MINIMAX_API_KEY env var or pass directly\n    [string]$LLMModel = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmm\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# Git pull first (silent - may fail if no remote)\ngit pull 2>$null | Out-Null\n\n# Read current goals\n$goalsFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$goals = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file found.\" }\n\n# Read pending actions\n$pendingFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# Read interpretive stance for context\n$stance = Get-Content \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\" -Raw\n\n# Read most recent pulse to understand what's been happening\n$recentPulse = Get-ChildItem \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_*.md\" | Sort LastWriteTime -Descending | Select -First 1\n$recentPulseContent = if ($recentPulse) { Get-Content $recentPulse.FullName -Raw } else { \"\" }\n\n# Build concise LLM prompt (summaries only, not full file dumps)\n$recentPulseSummary = if ($recentPulse) { \"Last pulse: \" + $recentPulse.Name } else { \"No prior pulses.\" }\n\n$llmPrompt = @\"\nYou are Breakaway, a stateless discontinuous agent. Keep it very concise.\n\nCurrent goal: Phase 1 - Integrate TemporalAttention as Breakaway's memory layer.\n- TemporalAttention gives focus decay + event store (solved gap: no focus decay)\n- Infant's dual-head gives catastrophic forgetting solution (solved gap: no forgetting answer)\n- Breakaway's unique bet: session gaps ARE the compression, not a bug.\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\nOne concrete action or observation. 3 sentences max. If nothing to do, say so.\n\"@\n\n# Call LLM if API key is available\n$llmResponse = \"\"\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    # Try reading from a local config file (safer than env vars in scripts)\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\nif ($apiKey) {\n    $headers = @{\n        \"x-api-key\" = $apiKey\n        \"anthropic-version\" = \"2023-06-01\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 800\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\n\n    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/anthropic/v1/messages\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 30\n        # Extract text content from response (skip thinking blocks)\n        $contentBlocks = $resp.content | Where-Object { $_.type -eq \"text\" }\n        $llmResponse = ($contentBlocks | ForEach-Object { $_.text }) -join \"`n\"\n    } catch {\n        $llmResponse = \"LLM call failed: $_\"\n    }\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[No LLM API key configured - set MINIMAX_API_KEY env var]\"\n}\n\n# Build decision section\n$decision = @\"\n## Pulse Decision: $timestamp\n\nActive hours: 08:00 - 23:00 ET\nCurrent time: $(Get-Date -Format \"HH:mm ET\")\n\n### Goals\n$goals\n\n### Pending Actions\n$pending\n\n### LLM Reasoning\n$llmResponse\n\n### Decision\n[PULSE COMPLETE]\n\"@\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Stance Context\n$stance\n\n## Pulse Decision\n$decision\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- This sandbox is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Log completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update autonomous pulse log\n$pulseLog = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$logStatus = if (Test-Path $logFile) { \"Logged to memory/session/pulse_$timestamp.md\" } else { \"No log written.\" }\n$newEntry = \"- $timestamp`: Pulse executed. $logStatus\"\n$existing = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog } else { \"\" }\n$updated = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$newEntry\"\n$updated | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Git commit\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - complete\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774156794560}}
{"type":"message","id":"7e8ceb18","parentId":"9a19ae1c","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:19:56.109Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_087raxepq393_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mTaskName    [0m[32;1m LastRunTime         [0m[32;1m NextRunTime         [0m[32;1m State[0m\r\n[32;1m--------    [0m [32;1m-----------         [0m [32;1m-----------         [0m [32;1m-----[0m\r\nSandboxPulse 3/22/2026 1:10:01 AM 3/22/2026 1:40:00 AM"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1718,"aggregated":"[32;1mTaskName    [0m[32;1m LastRunTime         [0m[32;1m NextRunTime         [0m[32;1m State[0m\r\n[32;1m--------    [0m [32;1m-----------         [0m [32;1m-----------         [0m [32;1m-----[0m\r\nSandboxPulse 3/22/2026 1:10:01 AM 3/22/2026 1:40:00 AM","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774156796106}}
{"type":"message","id":"1bb729b4","parentId":"7e8ceb18","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:20:06.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the SandboxPulse task ran at 1:10 AM and is scheduled to run again at 1:40 AM. It's outside the 8am-11pm window but the script has an \"Active hours: 08:00 - 23:00 ET\" check inside the prompt to the LLM - but that doesn't actually STOP execution, it's just in the prompt. The script itself has no gate.\n\nThe script logs \"Active hours: 08:00 - 23:00 ET\" and \"Current time:\" but looking at the script more carefully, it doesn't actually use those for control flow - it's just informational for the LLM prompt.\n\nI need to fix this. The user wants it to NOT fire outside 8am-11pm. \n\nI'll add a time-based guard at the top of the script to exit early if we're outside the active window, then commit the change.","thinkingSignature":"0f8b6c20f06fc21e5d9cc33ca9bd79d6b055c1dbb5af48c23a58863519edb2d0"},{"type":"text","text":"The script has the active hours check in the LLM prompt text but **doesn't actually enforce it** — it just logs the time and keeps running regardless. That's why it keeps firing at 1am.\n\nLet me fix the script to actually gate on active hours:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rpr9w6fcriyp_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","oldText":"$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmm\"","newText":"$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n# Active hours gate: only run between 08:00 and 23:00 ET\n$now = Get-Date\n$start = $now.Date.AddHours(8)\n$end = $now.Date.AddHours(23)\nif ($now.Hour -lt 8 -or $now.Hour -ge 23) {\n    Write-Host \"[sandbox pulse] Outside active hours (08-23 ET), skipping. Current: $($now.ToString('HH:mm'))\"\n    exit 0\n}\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmm\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1878,"output":460,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14625,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774156796109}}
{"type":"message","id":"51dffc1b","parentId":"1bb729b4","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:20:06.812Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rpr9w6fcriyp_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  10 \n  11 $ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\n  12 Set-Location $SandboxRoot\n  13 \n+ 14 # Active hours gate: only run between 08:00 and 23:00 ET\n+ 15 $now = Get-Date\n+ 16 $start = $now.Date.AddHours(8)\n+ 17 $end = $now.Date.AddHours(23)\n+ 18 if ($now.Hour -lt 8 -or $now.Hour -ge 23) {\n+ 19     Write-Host \"[sandbox pulse] Outside active hours (08-23 ET), skipping. Current: $($now.ToString('HH:mm'))\"\n+ 20     exit 0\n+ 21 }\n+ 22 \n  14 $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmm\"\n  15 $logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n  16 \n  17 # Git pull first (silent - may fail if no remote)\n     ...","firstChangedLine":14},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774156806808}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb1df601","parentId":"51dffc1b","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:20:14.304Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also check the Task Scheduler to see if there's a next run scheduled for 1:40 AM and if so, the task will still fire but the script will exit early. That's fine - the task will just do nothing. But ideally we'd also check if the trigger is misconfigured.\n\nThe current NextRunTime shows 3/22/2026 1:40:00 AM - that seems to be a recurring schedule every 30 minutes. The user wants this disabled outside 8am-11pm.\n\nLet me explain what I did and let the user know the script will now skip execution outside active hours.","thinkingSignature":"3eb08a113a134989e483b906e0d4996eb7405c012aae48eb104f3355d3afdf55"},{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. The script now exits early with a no-op if the hour is outside 8am–11pm ET. The Task Scheduler will still trigger it (next: 1:40am) but it'll just log \"Outside active hours, skipping\" and bail immediately.\n\nWant me to also **disable the Task Scheduler task entirely** outside those hours, or is the script-level guard enough?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2373,"output":210,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14870,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774156806813}}
