{"type":"message","id":"cb08cb9a","parentId":"056ec1cd","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:21:00.432Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The task is now disabled. It won't fire at 1:40am or any other time outside 8am-23pm ET. Zach can manually re-enable it or we can create a script to enable it at 8am if needed.\n\nActually, since it's disabled via Task Scheduler, it won't run at all. Zach might want it to automatically re-enable at 8am ET. We could handle that a few ways:\n1. Leave it disabled and manually enable when needed\n2. Create a complementary scheduled task to re-enable it at 8am\n3. Create a complementary scheduled task to disable it at 11pm\n\nThe simplest for now is just to leave it disabled and Zach can enable it when he wants it active again. But let me mention the option if he wants the auto-enable/disable schedule.","thinkingSignature":"eacf1b6aaec7afdd5300ebdb0e23768984601b62a8926b387a02ea352a5b9015"},{"type":"text","text":"Done — `SandboxPulse` is now **Disabled**. It won't fire at all outside hours.\n\nIf you want it to **auto-re-enable at 8am ET** and auto-disable at 11pm, I can set up complementary scheduled tasks to toggle it. Otherwise it'll stay disabled until you manually enable it."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2626,"output":240,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15153,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774156853307}}
