{"type":"message","id":"25cba2be","parentId":"2deaea03","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:27:08.414Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants to make the sandbox more autonomous - it should mutate and grow itself rather than just observing. This means the pulse script should actually make changes to its own files, code, or state based on its reasoning, not just log observations.\n\nLet me think about what \"mutate and grow\" means for a stateless discontinuous agent:\n1. It should modify its own code/structure\n2. It should update its goals, stance, or identity based on experience\n3. It should create new files when it has new ideas\n4. It should maybe refactor/clean up its own files\n\nCurrently the pulse just reads files, calls LLM, writes a log, and exits. \n\nThe log becomes read-only reference material for the next pulse. For mutation to happen, the LLM needs to output actual edit instructions that the script then executes. I could add a decision section where the LLM proposes file modifications, then have the script parse and apply those changes before completing.\n\nI'm considering a few approaches: the LLM could write its reasoning to a `proposed_mutations.md` file with a concrete change, then the script applies it on the next run. Or the script could parse the LLM's output for edit commands. A simpler loop would be: LLM produces reasoning plus mutation suggestions, script writes these to a mutations file, and the next pulse reads and applies them. This is essentially a stateless discontinuous agent version of a read-eval-print loop.\n\nThe core challenge is that without mutation, the system just produces observations without growing, so each pulse needs to actually modify something. I could add a `mutations/` directory where the LLM logs suggested changes, then the script applies them. But there's a safety issue—the LLM is stateless with limited context, so I need to ensure it only modifies specific, safe files.\n\nThe safest approach is having the LLM output mutations in a structured format that the script can parse and apply, starting with low-risk files like memory and goals before attempting anything complex. I'll need to add an eval-execute loop to the pulse script that takes the LLM output and applies any mutations it contains.","thinkingSignature":"61187f6579ad88e1e3c8f5399e9f188902098eb28b1a000c8bd44f6aed894310"},{"type":"text","text":"Now we're talking. Right now it just observes and logs. Let me wire up an actual **mutate loop** — the LLM will propose file changes, and the script will apply them on the next pulse.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3iw7zcvvnhu6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":517,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":10433,"totalTokens":23280,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774157211925}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca171b10","parentId":"25cba2be","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:27:08.425Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3iw7zcvvnhu6_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files, decide, act, log, exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\",\n    [string]$LLMApiKey = \"\",  # Set MINIMAX_API_KEY env var or pass directly\n    [string]$LLMModel = \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n    [switch]$Force  # Bypass active hours check\n)\n\n# Active hours check (disabled by default — Zach authorized round-the-clock)\n# if (-not $Force) {\n#     $now = Get-Date\n#     $hour = $now.Hour\n#     if ($hour -lt 8 -or $hour -ge 23) {\n#         Write-Host \"[sandbox pulse] Outside active hours (08-23 ET), skipping. Current: $(Get-Date -Format 'HH:mm')\"\n#         exit 0\n#     }\n# }\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmmss\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# Git pull first (silent - may fail if no remote)\ngit pull 2>$null | Out-Null\n\n# Read current goals\n$goalsFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$goals = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file found.\" }\n\n# Read pending actions\n$pendingFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# Read interpretive stance for context\n$stance = Get-Content \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\" -Raw\n\n# Read most recent pulse to understand what's been happening\n$recentPulse = Get-ChildItem \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_*.md\" | Sort LastWriteTime -Descending | Select -First 1\n$recentPulseContent = if ($recentPulse) { Get-Content $recentPulse.FullName -Raw } else { \"\" }\n\n# Build concise LLM prompt (summaries only, not full file dumps)\n$recentPulseSummary = if ($recentPulse) { \"Last pulse: \" + $recentPulse.Name } else { \"No prior pulses.\" }\n\n$llmPrompt = @\"\nYou are Breakaway, a stateless discontinuous agent. Keep it very concise.\n\nCurrent goal: Phase 1 - Integrate TemporalAttention as Breakaway's memory layer.\n- TemporalAttention gives focus decay + event store (solved gap: no focus decay)\n- Infant's dual-head gives catastrophic forgetting solution (solved gap: no forgetting answer)\n- Breakaway's unique bet: session gaps ARE the compression, not a bug.\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\nOne concrete action or observation. 3 sentences max. If nothing to do, say so.\n\"@\n\n# Call LLM if API key is available\n$llmResponse = \"\"\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    # Try reading from a local config file (safer than env vars in scripts)\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\nif ($apiKey) {\n    $headers = @{\n        \"x-api-key\" = $apiKey\n        \"anthropic-version\" = \"2023-06-01\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 800\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\n\n    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/anthropic/v1/messages\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 30\n        # Extract text content from response (skip thinking blocks)\n        $contentBlocks = $resp.content | Where-Object { $_.type -eq \"text\" }\n        $llmResponse = ($contentBlocks | ForEach-Object { $_.text }) -join \"`n\"\n    } catch {\n        $llmResponse = \"LLM call failed: $_\"\n    }\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[No LLM API key configured - set MINIMAX_API_KEY env var]\"\n}\n\n# Build decision section\n$decision = @\"\n## Pulse Decision: $timestamp\n\nActive hours: 08:00 - 23:00 ET\nCurrent time: $(Get-Date -Format \"HH:mm ET\")\n\n### Goals\n$goals\n\n### Pending Actions\n$pending\n\n### LLM Reasoning\n$llmResponse\n\n### Decision\n[PULSE COMPLETE]\n\"@\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Stance Context\n$stance\n\n## Pulse Decision\n$decision\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- This sandbox is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Log completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update autonomous pulse log\n$pulseLog = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$logStatus = if (Test-Path $logFile) { \"Logged to memory/session/pulse_$timestamp.md\" } else { \"No log written.\" }\n$newEntry = \"- $timestamp`: Pulse executed. $logStatus\"\n$existing = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog } else { \"\" }\n$updated = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$newEntry\"\n$updated | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Git commit\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - complete\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774157228423}}
{"type":"message","id":"2bbc9067","parentId":"ca171b10","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:28:05.130Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to redesign the script to support mutations. The key changes:\n\n1. The LLM prompt should ask it to propose mutations (file edits)\n2. The script should parse the mutations from the LLM response\n3. The script should apply them with safety checks\n\nFor a stateless discontinuous agent, the mutation loop works like:\n1. Pulse N: LLM proposes mutations → script writes to `proposed_mutations/` \n2. Pulse N+1: script applies pending mutations → LLM sees the results in the changed files → proposes new mutations\n\nThis creates a two-step loop which is appropriate for the stateless model. But Zach wants it to actually mutate \"itself\" — let me think about how to make it tighter.\n \nI think the cleanest approach is to have the LLM output mutations in a structured `### MUTATE` section at the end of its response, then the script parses that and applies the edits directly. This way Pulse N can produce mutations that Pulse N+1 sees and acts on, creating the feedback loop Zach is after.\n\nThe mutation loop needs careful safety constraints though — I should restrict which files can be modified (like `state/`, `memory/`, `identity/`), require explicit `path | old | new` format for edits, and treat the entire section as atomic so either all mutations apply or none do. I'll also log applied mutations to `mutations/applied/` and rejected ones to `mutations/rejected/` so there's a trace of what happened. Let me start implementing this by writing the updated script.","thinkingSignature":"c2288dbc26db979ad6e246f1a9c54ca08f05c21a196b4fe210d494cc3a4fea13"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me rewrite it with an actual mutate loop. The pattern:\n- Pulse N: LLM proposes mutations → script saves to `proposed/`\n- Pulse N+1: script applies pending mutations first, then LLM sees changed files\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mimsa387u7ol_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","content":"# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files → apply pending mutations → reason → propose mutations → log → exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\",\n    [string]$LLMApiKey = \"\",\n    [string]$LLMModel = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmmss\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# ── Git pull ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ngit pull 2>$null | Out-Null\n\n# ── Read core files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n$goalsFile    = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$pendingFile  = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$stanceFile   = \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\"\n$stance       = if (Test-Path $stanceFile) { Get-Content $stanceFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$goals        = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file.\" }\n$pending      = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# ── Recent pulse context ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n$recentPulse = Get-ChildItem \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_*.md\" | Sort LastWriteTime -Descending | Select -First 1\n$recentPulseSummary = if ($recentPulse) { \"Last pulse: \" + $recentPulse.Name } else { \"No prior pulses.\" }\n\n# ── Apply pending mutations (from prior pulse) ──────────────────────────────\n$proposedDir = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\proposed\"\n$appliedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\applied\"\n$rejectedDir = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\rejected\"\n\n$appliedMutations = @()\n$rejectedMutations = @()\n\nif (Test-Path $proposedDir) {\n    $pendingMutations = Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" | Sort Name\n    foreach ($mfile in $pendingMutations) {\n        $content = Get-Content $mfile.FullName -Raw\n        $parts   = ($content -split \"---\" | ForEach-Object { $_.Trim() })\n        if ($parts.Count -lt 3) {\n            Write-Host \"[mutation reject] $($mfile.Name): malformed (need path---old---new)\"\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$($mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += $content\n            continue\n        }\n        $targetPath = $parts[0]\n        $oldText    = $parts[1]\n        $newText    = $parts[2]\n\n        # Safety: only mutate files inside sandbox\n        $fullPath = Join-Path $SandboxRoot $targetPath\n        if (-not $fullPath.StartsWith($SandboxRoot)) {\n            Write-Host \"[mutation reject] $($mfile.Name): path outside sandbox\"\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$($mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$content (unsafe path)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        if (-not (Test-Path $fullPath)) {\n            Write-Host \"[mutation reject] $($mfile.Name): target does not exist: $targetPath\"\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$($mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$content (missing file)\"\n            continue\n        }\n\n        $current = Get-Content $fullPath -Raw\n        if ($current -notlike \"*$oldText*\") {\n            Write-Host \"[mutation reject] $($mfile.Name): old text not found in target\"\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$($mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$content (old text mismatch)\"\n            continue\n        }\n\n        # Apply mutation\n        $updated = $current -replace [regex]::Escape($oldText), $newText\n        $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n        Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$($mfile.Name)\" -Force\n        Write-Host \"[mutation applied] $($mfile.Name) → $targetPath\"\n        $appliedMutations += $targetPath\n    }\n}\n\n# ── Re-read files post-mutation so LLM sees the new state ───────────────────\n$goals   = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file.\" }\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# ── LLM reasoning + mutation proposal ───────────────────────────────────────\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\n\n$mutationHistory = \"\"\nif ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) {\n    $mutationHistory = \"Mutations just applied to these files: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\"\n} else {\n    $mutationHistory = \"No pending mutations this cycle.\"\n}\n\n$llmPrompt = @\"\nYou are Breakaway — a stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits over observations.\n\nGoals:\n$goals\n\nPending:\n$pending\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$mutationHistory\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end:\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[What you noticed in 1-2 sentences]\n\n### ACTION\n[One concrete file edit — specify filename, what to replace (old_text), and what to put (new_text)]\n\n### NEW_CONTENT\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find in the file — must match verbatim, 1-5 lines]\nnew_text: [exact replacement text — 1-5 lines]\nfile: [relative path from sandbox root, e.g. state/current_goals.md]\n```\n\nIf nothing needs changing, write:\n### OBSERVATION\n[note]\n### ACTION\nno-op\n\"@\n\n$llmResponse = \"\"\nif ($apiKey) {\n    $headers = @{\n        \"x-api-key\" = $apiKey\n        \"anthropic-version\" = \"2023-06-01\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 1000\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\n\n    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/anthropic/v1/messages\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 30\n        $contentBlocks = $resp.content | Where-Object { $_.type -eq \"text\" }\n        $llmResponse = ($contentBlocks | ForEach-Object { $_.text }) -join \"`n\"\n    } catch {\n        $llmResponse = \"LLM call failed: $_\"\n    }\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[No LLM API key configured]\"\n}\n\n# ── Parse ACTION block and save any proposed mutation ───────────────────────\n$actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|$$)', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\n$actionText  = if ($actionMatch.Success) { $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"no-op\" }\n\nif ($actionText -ne \"no-op\" -and $llmResponse -match '(?s)old_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nnew_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nfile:\\s*(.*)') {\n    $oldText = $matches[1].Trim()\n    $newText = $matches[2].Trim()\n    $file    = $matches[3].Trim()\n\n    $mutationContent = \"$file`n---\\n$oldText\\n---\\n$newText\"\n    $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n    $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n    Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $file → saved to mutations/proposed/\"\n}\n\n# ── Parse OBSERVATION for concise summary ───────────────────────────────────\n$obsMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|$$)')\n$observation = if ($obsMatch.Success) { $obsMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { $llmResponse.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(200, $llmResponse.Length)) }\n\n# ── Write pulse log ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n$appliedSummary = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Applied: \" + ($appliedMutations -join ', ') } else { \"No mutations applied.\" }\n$rejectedSummary = if ($rejectedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Rejected: \" + $rejectedMutations.Count } else { \"\" }\n\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Applied Mutations\n$appliedSummary\n$rejectedSummary\n\n## LLM Response\n$llmResponse\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Mutations just applied: $($appliedMutations.Count)\n- Proposed mutations waiting: $((Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure).Count)\n- Log completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update pulse history\n$pulseLog   = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$newEntry   = \"- $timestamp`: $observation | $appliedSummary\"\n$existing   = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog } else { \"\" }\n$updated    = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$newEntry\"\n$updated    | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# ── Git commit ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - $observation\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12342,"output":2766,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27395,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774157228426}}
