{"type":"message","id":"972fa53c","parentId":"cc826e0d","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:28:55.163Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The LLM proposed creating a new file (research/SIGNIFICANCE.md) but the regex didn't match the format because:\n1. It used `(new file)` instead of a proper old_text\n2. The new_text is multi-line and complex\n3. The file path wasn't extracted correctly\n\nThe regex for parsing was:\n```\n$llmResponse -match '(?s)old_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nnew_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nfile:\\s*(.*)'\n```\n\nBut the response had `old_text: (new file)` and then multiline content. The issue is the regex expects `old_text:` followed immediately by newline, but `(new file)` is inline.\n\n\nI need to adjust the parsing to handle `(new file)` as a special marker, allow multi-line content for new_text, and properly capture the file path from the end of the response. Let me trace through what the full LLM response actually looks like to understand where the regex is failing.","thinkingSignature":"0d176adb9da0a9598dce2153da2b101eb76cd8e69930ea0763348f8fb9186c59"},{"type":"text","text":"The LLM **did propose a mutation** — a new `research/SIGNIFICANCE.md` file — but the regex didn't catch it because the format was slightly off. Let me fix the parser:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3vk15ukcr33e_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-22 012814.md","offset":60,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17275,"output":322,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29884,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774157323503}}
