{"type":"message","id":"9bb40750","parentId":"c8b0177d","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:29:16.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The LLM output was a multi-line block with `old_text: (new file)` and `file: research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md`. The regex didn't match because:\n1. The `old_text: (new file)` is on the same line as `old_text:`, not a separate line\n2. The file path has a different name than I expected\n\nLet me fix the regex to handle:\n1. `old_text: (new file)` as a special case for new files\n2. Multi-line new_text content\n\nThe regex was:\n```\n$llmResponse -match '(?s)old_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nnew_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nfile:\\s*(.*)'\n\n\n```\n\nBut the actual format was:\n```\nold_text: (new file)\nnew_text: # Significance Scoring for Pulse Content\n...multi-line content...\nfile: research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\n```\n\nThe issue is `old_text: (new file)` has `old_text:` and `(new file)` on the same line, while the regex expects `\\n` after `old_text:`. I need to make the pattern more flexible to handle both cases where the old text appears on the same line as the label or on the next line, and then capture multi-line content for new_text until the file: directive appears.\n\n```\n$llmResponse -match '(?s)old_text:\\s*(?:\\((.*?)\\)|\\n(.*?)\\n)new_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nfile:\\s*(.*)'\n```\n\nThis should handle the `(new file)` case by capturing the filename in group 1 when it exists, or falling back to group 2 for the multi-line old text format.","thinkingSignature":"c5d371de8617f0402d5b2a6aa15ea8104b33cfc30211485c4babd12d8e4c27f3"},{"type":"text","text":"The parser missed it — the LLM used `old_text: (new file)` on the same line. Let me fix the regex to handle that:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hduc9v5e4ffz_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","oldText":"$actionText  = if ($actionMatch.Success) { $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"no-op\" }\n\nif ($actionText -ne \"no-op\" -and $llmResponse -match '(?s)old_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nnew_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nfile:\\s*(.*)') {\n    $oldText = $matches[1].Trim()\n    $newText = $matches[2].Trim()\n    $file    = $matches[3].Trim()\n\n    $mutationContent = \"$file`n---\\n$oldText`n---\\n$newText\"\n    $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n    $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n    Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $file → saved to mutations/proposed/\"\n}","newText":"$actionText  = if ($actionMatch.Success) { $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"no-op\" }\n\n# Parse mutation: handles \"old_text: (new file)\" or \"old_text:\\n<multiline>\"\nif ($actionText -ne \"no-op\" -and $llmResponse -match '(?s)old_text:\\s*(?:\\(([^)]+)\\)|([^\\n]*\\n.*?))\\nnew_text:\\s*\\n(.*?)\\nfile:\\s*(.*)') {\n    $isNewFile  = $matches[1] -eq \"new file\"\n    $oldText    = if ($isNewFile) { \"[NEW_FILE]\" } else { $matches[2].Trim() }\n    $newText    = $matches[3].Trim()\n    $file       = $matches[4].Trim()\n\n    if ($isNewFile) {\n        $mutationContent = \"$file`n---\\n[NEW_FILE]`n---\\n$newText\"\n    } else {\n        $mutationContent = \"$file`n---\\n$oldText`n---\\n$newText\"\n    }\n    $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n    $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n    Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $file → saved to mutations/proposed/\"\n}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17776,"output":953,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31016,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774157335175}}
