{"type":"message","id":"2a38258e","parentId":"fb65dcec","timestamp":"2026-03-22T05:36:44.368Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture. The MUTATION block goes from `### MUTATION` to the end, but there's NO `file:` line. The LLM described what file to create in the ACTION (`Create research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md`) but didn't include the `file:` directive in the MUTATION block.\n\nThis is a consistent problem: the LLM gets distracted by the multi-line content and forgets to add the `file:` line. I need to handle this.\n\nTwo approaches:\n1. If `file:` is missing but the MUTATION block otherwise looks valid, try to infer the file from the ACTION text\n\n\n2. Make the LLM more reliable at including `file:`\n3. Make the parser smarter - look for the file path mentioned in the ACTION block\n\nThe simplest fix is to fall back to parsing the ACTION block for something like `Create research/XXX.md` and use that as the file path. I'll update the parser to handle this - if `file:` isn't found in the MUTATION block, I'll search the ACTION section for a file path pattern and extract it from there.\n\nWait, I think the real issue is that the LLM is putting the file path inside the fenced code block itself. Looking at the raw output more carefully, the closing fence appears after the table, and then the next section starts, which means the file path is getting cut off or misplaced. I need to trace through the actual character positions to see where the file directive should appear. I'm realizing the `file:` line might actually be positioned inside the second code fence rather than after it—the ANSI escape codes are making the structure hard to parse visually. Let me trace through the regex pattern more carefully to see where the `file:` directive should actually appear in the formatted output. I'm realizing the ANSI escape sequences are making it hard to track where exactly the closing fence sits relative to the content. The `[0m` resets formatting, and `[7m` inverts colors—these are just display effects, not actual content characters. Let me just write the full mutation block to a temp file so I can see the raw structure without the escape codes muddying things up.","thinkingSignature":"d5bf4dcec3e337397bb5510e8662df3947c78bae5185800edcf2cebc0bce5a62"},{"type":"text","text":"The `file:` line is missing from the LLM output entirely. The LLM gets lost in the multi-line content and forgets to add it. Let me fix the parser to fall back to the ACTION block when `file:` is missing:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iv3fp75izp5w_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","oldText":"# Parse MUTATION block — extract old_text, new_text (multiline), and file from the block\n$mutationProposed = $false\n$mStart = $llmResponse.IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ($mStart -ge 0) {\n    $block = $llmResponse.Substring($mStart)\n    # Remove code fences if present\n    $block = $block -replace '(?s)```.*?```', ''\n    # Extract fields\n    $oldMatch = [regex]::Match($block, 'old_text:\\s*(.+)')\n    $fileMatch = [regex]::Match($block, 'file:\\s*(.+)')\n    $oldLine = if ($oldMatch.Success) { $oldMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    $fileLine = if ($fileMatch.Success) { $fileMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    # new_text: everything between \"new_text:\" line and \"file:\" line\n    $newText = \"\"\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine) {\n        $ntMatch = [regex]::Match($block, '(?s)new_text:\\s*\\n(.+?)\\s*\\n\\s*file:', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\n        if ($ntMatch.Success) { $newText = $ntMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\n    }\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine -and $newText) {\n        if ($oldLine -eq \"(new file)\") {\n            $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n[NEW_FILE]`n---`n$newText\"\n        } else {\n            $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n$oldLine`n---`n$newText\"\n        }\n        $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n        $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $fileLine\"\n        $mutationProposed = $true\n    }\n}","newText":"# Parse MUTATION block — extract old_text, new_text (multiline), and file from the block\n$mutationProposed = $false\n$mStart = $llmResponse.IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ($mStart -ge 0) {\n    $block = $llmResponse.Substring($mStart)\n    # Remove ALL code fences (replace each fence pair with placeholder, repeat until stable)\n    $prev = \"\"\n    while ($prev -ne $block) { $prev = $block; $block = $block -replace '(?s)```.*?```', \"`n[CODE_BLOCK]`n\" }\n    # Extract fields\n    $oldMatch = [regex]::Match($block, 'old_text:\\s*(.+)')\n    $fileMatch = [regex]::Match($block, 'file:\\s*(.+)')\n    $oldLine = if ($oldMatch.Success) { $oldMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    $fileLine = if ($fileMatch.Success) { $fileMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    # new_text: between \"new_text:\" line and \"file:\" line (after fence removal)\n    $newText = \"\"\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine) {\n        $ntMatch = [regex]::Match($block, '(?s)new_text:\\s*\\n(.+?)\\s*\\n\\s*file:', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\n        if ($ntMatch.Success) { $newText = $ntMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\n    }\n    # Fallback: if file missing, try to extract from ACTION block\n    if (-not $fileLine) {\n        $actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|$)')\n        if ($actionMatch.Success) {\n            $actionText = $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value\n            $fileInference = [regex]::Match($actionText, '(?:Create|Edit|Update)\\s+(?:`)?([^\\s`]+)(?:`)?')\n            if ($fileInference.Success) { $fileLine = $fileInference.Groups[1].Value }\n        }\n    }\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine -and $newText) {\n        if ($oldLine -eq \"(new file)\") {\n            $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n[NEW_FILE]`n---`n$newText\"\n        } else {\n            $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n$oldLine`n---`n$newText\"\n        }\n        $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n        $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $fileLine\"\n        $mutationProposed = $true\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old_text=$oldLine file=$fileLine new_text_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n    }\n}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39838,"output":1665,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53790,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774157771458}}
