`file:` line when content is long. The parser's ACTION-based fallback is matching \"a\" instead of the path. Let me fix both the regex and make the LLM prompt more explicit:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_soa8ijnqlajd_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","oldText":"    # Fallback: if file missing, try to extract from ACTION block\n    if (-not $fileLine) {\n        $actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|$)')\n        if ($actionMatch.Success) {\n            $actionText = $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value\n            $fileInference = [regex]::Match($actionText, '(?:Create|Edit|Update)\\s+(?:`)?([^\\s`]+)(?:`)?')\n            if ($fileInference.Success) { $fileLine = $fileInference.Groups[1].Value }\n        }\n    }","newText":"    # Fallback: if file missing, try to extract from ACTION block\n    if (-not $fileLine) {\n        $actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|$)')\n        if ($actionMatch.Success) {\n            $actionText = $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value\n            # Match \"Create `path/file.md`\" or \"Edit `path/file.md`\" with or without backticks\n            $fileInference = [regex]::Match($actionText, '(?:Create|Edit|Update|New file)[:\\s]+(?:``([^``]+)``|([^\\s]+))')\n            if ($fileInference.Success) {\n                $fileLine = if ($fileInference.Groups[2].Value) { $fileInference.Groups[2].Value } else { $fileInference.Groups[1].Value }\n                Write-Host \"[file inferred from ACTION] $fileLine\"\n            }\n        }\n    }"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41903,"output":830,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55020,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774160521998}}
