{"type":"message","id":"3f55baad","parentId":"55efba99","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:23:27.318Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_quk9fe8bxd42_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\r\n  \"id\": \"060ebddd16ba0d89591e4e9669baa59f\",\r\n  \"choices\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"finish_reason\": \"length\",\r\n      \"index\": 0,\r\n      \"message\": {\r\n        \"content\": \"<think>\\nThe user asks: \\\"Say hello in 5 words\\\". That is a simple request. They want a greeting expressed in 5 words. Possibly \\\"Hello there, how are you?\\\" That's 5 words? Let's count: \\\"Hello\\\" (1), \\\"there,\\\" (2), \\\"how\\\" (3), \\\"are\\\" (4), \\\"you?\\\" (5). That's 5 words (assuming punctuation doesn't count). Another could be \\\"Hey, good morning, friend!\\\" That's more\\n</think>\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"role\": \"assistant\",\r\n        \"name\": \"MiniMax AI\",\r\n        \"audio_content\": \"\"\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"created\": 1774160605,\r\n  \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\r\n  \"object\": \"chat.completion\",\r\n  \"usage\": {\r\n    \"total_tokens\": 147,\r\n    \"total_characters\": 0,\r\n    \"prompt_tokens\": 47,\r\n    \"completion_tokens\": 100,\r\n    \"completion_tokens_details\": {\r\n      \"reasoning_tokens\": 100\r\n    },\r\n    \"prompt_tokens_details\": {\r\n      \"cached_tokens\": 0\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  \"input_sensitive\": false,\r\n  \"output_sensitive\": false,\r\n  \"input_sensitive_type\": 0,\r\n  \"output_sensitive_type\": 0,\r\n  \"output_sensitive_int\": 0,\r\n  \"base_resp\": {\r\n    \"status_code\": 0,\r\n    \"status_msg\": \"\"\r\n  }\r\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3354,"aggregated":"{\r\n  \"id\": \"060ebddd16ba0d89591e4e9669baa59f\",\r\n  \"choices\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"finish_reason\": \"length\",\r\n      \"index\": 0,\r\n      \"message\": {\r\n        \"content\": \"<think>\\nThe user asks: \\\"Say hello in 5 words\\\". That is a simple request. They want a greeting expressed in 5 words. Possibly \\\"Hello there, how are you?\\\" That's 5 words? Let's count: \\\"Hello\\\" (1), \\\"there,\\\" (2), \\\"how\\\" (3), \\\"are\\\" (4), \\\"you?\\\" (5). That's 5 words (assuming punctuation doesn't count). Another could be \\\"Hey, good morning, friend!\\\" That's more\\n</think>\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"role\": \"assistant\",\r\n        \"name\": \"MiniMax AI\",\r\n        \"audio_content\": \"\"\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"created\": 1774160605,\r\n  \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\r\n  \"object\": \"chat.completion\",\r\n  \"usage\": {\r\n    \"total_tokens\": 147,\r\n    \"total_characters\": 0,\r\n    \"prompt_tokens\": 47,\r\n    \"completion_tokens\": 100,\r\n    \"completion_tokens_details\": {\r\n      \"reasoning_tokens\": 100\r\n    },\r\n    \"prompt_tokens_details\": {\r\n      \"cached_tokens\": 0\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  \"input_sensitive\": false,\r\n  \"output_sensitive\": false,\r\n  \"input_sensitive_type\": 0,\r\n  \"output_sensitive_type\": 0,\r\n  \"output_sensitive_int\": 0,\r\n  \"base_resp\": {\r\n    \"status_code\": 0,\r\n    \"status_msg\": \"\"\r\n  }\r\n}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774160607314}}
{"type":"message","id":"fa91a1e2","parentId":"3f55baad","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:23:43.871Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API call works fine when I test it directly. But in the pulse script, it's returning an empty `$llmResponse`. The issue is likely that `$resp.choices` is returning a nested structure. Looking at the raw response:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"choices\": [\n    {\n      \"index\": 0,\n      \"finish_reason\": \"stop\",\n      \"message\": {\n        \"role\": \"assistant\",\n        \"content\": \"\\n\\nHello! How can I help you today?\",\n        \"name\": \"MiniMax AI\",\n        \"audio_content\": \"\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nSo `$resp.choices` returns an array with one element. \n\nAh, I see the problem now—when I iterate through `$choices` with `ForEach-Object { $_.message.content }`, each item is actually an `Expand-Object` result, not the original object. So `$_` is a `PSCustomObject` with a `message` property, but `$_.message.content` is returning the content directly as a hashtable instead of a string. I need to trace through what `$resp.choices` actually produces when I expand it.\n\nLooking at the actual response structure, each choice has a `finish_reason` of \"stop\" and a `message` object with `content`, which suggests the MiniMax API might be wrapping the content differently than expected—possibly as a hashtable in the `content` field rather than a direct string property.\n\nWhen `Invoke-RestMethod` deserializes this into PSCustomObjects, the content field becomes a string like `\"Hello there, how are you?\"` rather than a hashtable, so the extraction should work as intended. I need to verify whether the actual `$llmResponse` variable is actually empty or if something else is preventing the content from being captured.","thinkingSignature":"eaaede9b59f529e89aa4b05a61c327a0e0e5a509978a1b9316e0f49ad8b8aab7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7lwi10kianir_1","name":"exec","arguments":{