{"type":"message","id":"71fc2398","parentId":"9a66c8ee","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:24:06.348Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the API works and the parsing works. The issue is the prompt is long and the LLM is outputting thinking blocks, and the max_tokens might be too low for the long prompt. Let me think about why the 02:22 pulse had empty LLM response.\n\nThe previous pulse at 02:21 had a valid response (mutation parse failed because file was missing). The 02:22 pulse returned empty. This could be because:\n1. The prompt is getting very long (lots of goals, pending items, recent pulse summaries) and the LLM is hitting the max_tokens limit\n2. Or the model is outputting a thinking block and the content extraction is failing\n\nLooking at the 02:22 log, the LLM Response section is completely empty, not even an error message. \n\nThe response might be truncated or malformed, causing the content field to become empty after deserialization. Rather than debug the parsing further, I should test the actual pulse script with a simple mutation to see what's really happening, or check if the response object itself is the problem.\n\nLet me run the pulse script again and focus on what actually gets returned.","thinkingSignature":"888191eb42528f78163cae270059e7e6d879cad27b3702311590be5fd43f1838"},{"type":"text","text":"\nAPI and parsing work fine in isolation. The issue is likely the prompt is getting too long — hitting max_tokens. Let me check the prompt size and trim it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g8a37dkceh15_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$prompt = @\"\nYou are Breakaway — stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- Lambda parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: .llm_key, pulse.ps1\n\n## Pending\n- Tune lambda empirically\n- Implement significance scoring\n- Wire to TemporalAttention backend\n\nRecent: Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-22 022128.md\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\nold_text: [exact text to find or \"(new file)\"]\nnew_text: [replacement text, keep concise]\nfile: [required — relative path from sandbox root]\n\"@; [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetByteCount($prompt)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46736,"output":680,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59703,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774160630386}}
