{"type":"message","id":"3b79ea85","parentId":"67588ec9","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:24:21.156Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The prompt is only 1575 bytes. That's very small. So the prompt length isn't the issue. The issue must be something else.\n\nLet me look at the 02:22 pulse log more carefully. The LLM Response is empty but the git commit happened. Let me look at what the response was.\n\nActually, looking at the end of the 02:22 pulse log - the `## LLM Response` section is completely empty, but the rest of the log is written. The `$llmResponse` variable must have been empty. But the API call should have worked...\n\nWait, maybe the issue is with the `messages` format. The MiniMax API might need a different format for the `role` field. Let me check if `system` role is supported.\n \nI'm wondering if the model is outputting content in a way that doesn't parse correctly - maybe the thinking block is being included in the message content itself. Let me check what the actual response structure looks like when I deserialize it, since `$resp.choices[0].message.content` might be structured differently than expected.\n\nLooking at the test results, the MiniMax model wraps its response in a thinking block first, so the actual content I need is nested deeper. I should adjust my extraction logic to account for this - instead of just taking the first choice's content directly, I might need to parse further or handle the nested structure differently. Though the test showed it worked fine, so maybe I should just add some debug logging to the script to see what's actually being returned.","thinkingSignature":"849859e10c3bd998350a68fe40ac683bfe17167f2b9a76ddbf264cdfe6873ef9"},{"type":"text","text":"The prompt is tiny — not a size issue. Let me add debug output and test directly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tnogeeibqmmu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$apiKey = \"sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0\"; $headers = @{ \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $apiKey\"; \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\" }; $body = @{ model = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"; max_tokens = 800; messages = @(@{role=\"user\"; content=\"You are Breakaway. Reply with exactly:\\n### OBSERVATION\\ntest obs\\n### ACTION\\nCreate research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\\n### MUTATION\\nold_text: (new file)\\nnew_text: # Significance Scoring\\nSignificance determines what survives.\\nfile: research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\"}) } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5; $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 30; Write-Host \"Choices: $($resp.choices.Count)\"; Write-Host \"Content type: $($resp.choices[0].message.content.GetType().Name)\"; Write-Host \"Content: $($resp.choices[0].message.content.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(200, $resp.choices[0].message.content.Length)))\"","timeout":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47434,"output":698,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60419,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774160646793}}
