{"type":"message","id":"d544eda9","parentId":"fc0bbc4d","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:24:44.109Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the content IS a string and it's returning correctly. The issue must be in the pulse script where the response is being processed differently. Let me check if the issue is the `$resp` variable scope or if the response is actually a different type in the script context.\n\nWait - in the pulse script, the `$resp` is defined inside an `if ($apiKey)` block. And then `$llmResponse` is set based on `$resp.choices`. Let me check if there's a JSON serialization issue with `ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5` for the body.\n\nActually, I wonder if the issue is that `ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5` with a nested object is not properly serializing the messages array. Let me check if the body is correct by looking at it.\n\n\nLet me just add some debug output to the script and run it again to see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"46edbad073370033e4a6aaa71db68a4c59dde9a767cba7b0941db5c6305b94ed"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pw2az7xv6knt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test the full pulse script flow with a debug version\n$apiKey = \"sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0\"\n$headers = @{ \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $apiKey\"; \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\" }\n$llmPrompt = \"You are Breakaway. Reply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: include file: line in MUTATION.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[file edit]\n\n### MUTATION\n```\nold_text: (new file)\nnew_text: # Significance Scoring\nNew scoring system for pulse content.\nfile: research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\n```\"\n\n$body = @{\n    model = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"\n    max_tokens = 800\n    messages = @(@{role=\"user\"; content=$llmPrompt})\n} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\n\n$resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 30\n$choices = $resp.choices\n$llmResponse = ($choices | ForEach-Object { $_.message.content }) -join \"`n\"\nWrite-Host \"[choices: $($choices.Count)]\"\nWrite-Host \"[response length: $($llmResponse.Length)]\"\nWrite-Host \"[first 300 chars]\"\nWrite-Host $llmResponse.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(300, $llmResponse.Length))","timeout":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48216,"output":605,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61108,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774160670122}}
