{"type":"message","id":"c310b6df","parentId":"926b0da4","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:25:51.518Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the direct test works. The content is returned properly. Now the issue in the pulse script must be that the `$body` passed to `Invoke-RestMethod` is a JSON string, not a byte array. Let me check if that's the issue.\n\nIn the pulse script:\n```powershell\n$body = @{ ... } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\n...\nInvoke-RestMethod -Uri \"...\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 60\n```\n\nIn my test:\n```powershell\n$b = @{ ... } | ConvertTo-Json -Compress\nInvoke-RestMethod -Uri \"...\" -Method Post -Headers $h -Body ([System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes($b)) -ContentType \"application/json\"\n\n\n```\n\nThe difference is I'm encoding the body as UTF-8 bytes with explicit ContentType, while the script is passing the JSON string directly. Let me try running a simplified version that matches exactly what the script does to see if that causes the issue.","thinkingSignature":"f26f4e820633644d2d10a6a0fc899dd78fcf6dad67dd3e5d2c88ef072cb7a640"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_14pkfgjrkle1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$key = \"sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0\"; $h = @{ \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $key\"; \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\" }; $b = @{ model = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"; max_tokens = 500; messages = @(@{role=\"user\"; content=\"Say hello and nothing else. Keep it under 10 words.\"}) } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5; $r = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $h -Body $b -TimeoutSec 15; Write-Host \"Content: '$($r.choices[0].message.content)'\"","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51968,"output":465,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64720,"