{"type":"message","id":"10ec9c81","parentId":"8d233f7a","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:29:27.044Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the order is:\n1. `$appliedMutations` is populated\n2. `$goals` and `$pending` are (re-)read\n3. `$appliedInfo` is set\n4. `$llmPrompt` here-string is created with all the variables\n\nThis should be fine. All variables are set before the here-string.\n\nBut wait - `$goals` and `$pending` are being RE-read from files AFTER the mutations are applied. So they contain the updated content. That's correct.\n\nHmm. Let me look at the `$appliedInfo` more carefully:\n```powershell\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n\n```\n\nThis is fine - it's a simple string.\n\nOK, I'm genuinely stumped. The API works in isolation but not in the script. Let me try adding some explicit debug output to see what's actually being sent. Actually, I just realized something - the error happens at line 142, which is inside the `Invoke-RestMethod` call. The error says `$choices[0]` is null, but that shouldn't be evaluated unless `$choices` itself is null. Unless... the error message is coming from somewhere else entirely.\n\nWait, looking at the output again - the error message itself contains variable expansion. The `$choices[0]` inside the string literal is what's being reported, not what's causing the crash. So the real issue is that `$resp.choices` is null or doesn't have a `[0]` index. The API itself is returning something that doesn't have the expected choices structure.\n\nI'm wondering if this could be a character encoding issue with the goals file. If it contains special Unicode characters that don't serialize properly through `ConvertTo-Json`, the request body might be malformed. Or maybe the MiniMax API is occasionally returning an error response in a different format, and when `Invoke-RestMethod` deserializes it, the structure doesn't match what I'm expecting.\n\n```\nActually, let me try adding error handling to see the actual raw response when this happens.\n```","thinkingSignature":"9c936a91191639188bfede67426d28808cc997425725d58ec559695d02269d58"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check if the raw HTTP response is different when it fails:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pdtmirn0t3on_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","oldText":"    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 60\n        Write-Host \"[DEBUG] resp keys: $($resp.PSObject.Properties.Name -join ', ')\"\n        $choices = $resp.choices\n        if ($null -ne $choices -and $choices.Count -gt 0) {\n            $rawContent = $choices[0].message.content\n            if ($null -eq $rawContent) {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content is NULL. Full choice: $($choices[0] | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n                $llmResponse = \"\"\n            } else {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content length: $($rawContent.Length)\"\n                $llmResponse = $rawContent\n            }\n        } else {\n            Write-Host \"[DEBUG] No choices. Full resp: $($resp | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n            $llmResponse = \"No choices: $($resp | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n        }\n    } catch {\n        $llmResponse = \"LLM call failed: $_\"\n    }","newText":"    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -"},"partialJson":"{\"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Zwmar\\\\.openclaw\\\\sandbox\\\\pulse.ps1\", \"oldText\": \"    try {\\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \\\"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\\\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 60\\n        Write-Host \\\"[DEBUG] resp keys: $($resp.PSObject.Properties.Name -join ', ')\\\"\\n        $choices = $resp.choices\\n        if ($null -ne $choices